# Campus Device Loan System
Student Name: Arshad Aslam
Student ID: K0352250
Module: Cloud Native DevOps (CIS3039-N)
University: Teesside University

## Project Overview
This project implements a simple cloud-native style Campus Device Loan System.
The system allows users to view available campus devices and reserve them using a lightweight API service.
The architecture separates the system into different services to demonstrate cloud-native and DevOps development practices.
The system includes an API service, a background worker service, automated tests, and supporting documentation that explains the system architecture and deployment design.

## System Architecture
The system is composed of three main components.
Web Interface  
Provides a simple frontend interface that displays available devices retrieved from the API.
API Service  
Handles device data, reservation functionality, and exposes system endpoints.
Worker Service  
Processes reservation events asynchronously and simulates background processing similar to microservice architectures.
Architecture diagrams are included in the Documentation folder and follow the C4 model approach.

