## Source Code Structure

API Service
Location:
Source/api
Responsible for:
device listing endpoint
single device endpoint
reservation endpoint
health monitoring endpoint
protected endpoint example
Example endpoints:
/devices
/devices/:id
/health
/admin

Worker Service
Location:
Source/worker
The worker simulates asynchronous event processing. When a reservation event is created the worker processes the event and outputs confirmation in the console.
This demonstrates background processing similar to message-driven systems used in microservice architectures.

Frontend
Location:
Source/api/public/index.html
A simple HTML interface used to display available devices retrieved from the API service.

Automated Tests
Location:
Source/tests/api.test.js
Automated tests verify the API behaviour including:
health endpoint
device list endpoint
single device endpoint
protected admin endpoint
Tests can be executed using:
npm test

